# Newronaut model tiering for Codex.
# Map each logical tier to a real Codex model slug (e.g. gpt-5.4, gpt-5.4-codex, gpt-5-mini).
# Leave a value BLANK to omit --model for that tier, i.e. use whatever model your Codex
# config/profile defaults to. Run `codex --help` or check your config.toml for valid slugs.
#
# MODEL_HIGH_ALT MUST differ from MODEL_HIGH for the red-team to genuinely avoid the build
# lineage's blind spots. If left blank it falls back to MODEL_HIGH (weaker guarantee).

MODEL_HIGH=""
MODEL_HIGH_ALT=""
MODEL_MID=""
MODEL_LOW=""
